node.text:
Real women. True stories.
Over the last couple of years I worked with @billabongwomens on the ‘Know The Feeling’ Series that took us around the world to meet inspiring women who are breaking culture norms through surfing and beyond.
These woman are truly paving the way for the next generation of women in their countries and I can’t wait to hear more stories and meet more amazing humans when we are able to travel again (one day ahh🤞🏼) - 
In the meantime feel free share stories below and to tag some women/organisations doing wonderful work in your community 🖤

EP 4 COMING FRIDAY!!!@patti_agency @willadlerphotographs @pigeon_research @billabongwomens
#knowthefeeling

node.text: Mother ocean has been alive this week at home! We really got it all. A big bombie swell, a freezing cold snap, wild winds & pretty sunsets (plus some windburn neck tans + whiplash). Fun sharing the lineup with everyone! Also thanks @chrisenever for carrying the heavier board down the beach for me haha 🌊🌊🌊🌊 Pic @fabiosilvestre

node.text:
Hi everyone! Letting you know there is still time to sign up for the @surfaid make a wave challenge :) This September join us in surfing every day for 30 days to raise funds for families in remote surf communities in Indonesia to access basic healthcare, clean water, sanitation and food security. Anyone, anywhere can join in so grab your friends and get involved. 
Check out the link in my bio for more info and how to sign up.
Pic @mattydunbar
@billabong_australia @billabong_womens_australia

HAPPY 30th @chloechapman !! WE LOVE YOU! What a wild hoot it’s been. together through all the laughter, the tears (and the random injuries) 🤣🖤 you are a absolute weapon and the best is yet to come darlingggg 🌈 I wish I could be celebrating with you today but going through old footage the last couple of days has had me in stitches so thankyouuuu 🤣
